Symphony, a Nollywood blockbuster musical movie with youth and music as its theme, is set to hit cinemas on September 9, 2022. Symphony is a beautiful and well-told story about life, love, dreams, success, trials, societal failure and the resultant effects. The movie reflects the travails of a typical talented African youth, struggling to overcome all odds in order to achieve breakthrough. Shot in exotic locations across Lagos, it parades an array of African stars such as D’banj, Jackie Appiah, Tanasha, Donna, Lanre Hassan, Bolaji Amusan (Mr. Latin), Kalu Ikeagu, Efa Iwara, Scarlet, Gomez, Daniel Abua and Doris Okorie. Also set to premiere with the film is an album comprising original soundtracks and performances from the project, written, recorded and performed by top stars, some of who featured in the movie. According to the film’s director, Oraka Nvy Nnanyelu, “Symphony is a beautifully crafted, priceless work of art that mirrors the African youth’s journey to relevance.”